# 5. 意思表示の果てに

Mafuyu: (I don't understand...)
Mafuyu: (When I was coming home from cram school, my chest felt so cold...)
Mafuyu: (But I feel so much warmer after talking with them.)
Mafuyu: (If only things could stay this way forever...)
Mafuyu: Oh, a message...
Mafuyu's Mother: I believe in you, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu's Mother: Because you know what you have to do in order to make your dream come true.
Ena: What's wrong...?
Mafuyu: I should head home. It's almost curfew...
Mizuki: Oh, it's already that late...?
Mizuki: Are you sure you're gonna be okay, Mafuyu...?
Mafuyu: Yes, I feel a little better now... Thank you both very much.
Ena: Alright, we've finished eating, so I guess we should head home too...
Mizuki: Okay. Let's go!
Mizuki: I had so much fun today. I hope we get to hang out like this again soon!
Mafuyu: Me too...
Mafuyu: ...
Ena: Hey, Mafuyu...?
Mafuyu: Yes...?
Ena: I know things aren't gonna be easy now that your mom knows about N25, but...
Ena: You need to speak up if something really bothers you.
Ena: Because you're the only one who can protect yourself in the end...
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: Okay...
Mafuyu: (I have to speak up if something bothers me...)
Mafuyu: (If something... Bothers me...)
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: (If I'm not allowed to do anything with N25...)
Mafuyu: (If I'm not allowed to make music with them, I...)
Mafuyu's Mother: Mafuyu... Why don't you stop staying up so late each night to study?
Mafuyu: Oh, I need to buy that study guide...
???: Mafuyu...?
Mafuyu: Huh...?
Mafuyu's Father: Fancy seeing you here. Are you just on your way home from cram school?
Mafuyu: Oh, Dad... Yes, but I need to go buy a study guide first.
Mafuyu's Father: I see. You're such a studious girl. Since I'm here, why don't I buy it for you?
Mafuyu: Oh...
Mafuyu: Thank you, Dad...
Mafuyu's Mother: Okay, you two. I made your favorite today. Beef stew. Bon appetit and don't be afraid to ask for seconds.
Mafuyu's Father: Thank you, dear.
Mafuyu: Thank you, Mom. It's delicious.
Mafuyu's Mother: Hehe. I'm glad to hear that. Still, I was surprised to see you both come home together.
Mafuyu: Thank you for buying me that study guide, Dad. I promise to put it to good use.
Mafuyu's Mother: That's wonderful, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu's Father: But you seem to have been staying up late to study recently. It's important to take breaks from time to time, okay?
Mafuyu: Oh...
Mafuyu's Mother: That's okay, dear. I've already spoken to her about that.
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes, it's important to study as much as you can before exams, but you need to rest instead of staying up so late.
Mafuyu's Mother: Right, Mafuyu?
Mafuyu: Um...
Ena: You need to speak up if something really bothers you.
Mafuyu's Father: Is something the matter, Mafuyu?
Mafuyu: Oh, um... Actually...
Mafuyu: Being barred from studying at night is...
Mafuyu: Not what I want...
Mafuyu's Mother: Oh? Why's that...?
Mafuyu: S-So, um... It's just... I think I should study whenever I can in preparation for my exams...
Mafuyu: The medical school I want to get into is extremely competitive, so I fear that I won't get in if I don't work harder than the other applicants.
Mafuyu's Mother: ...
Mafuyu's Father: Yes, I understand what you're trying to say. Your fellow applicants will surely be studying very hard to get accepted.
Mafuyu's Mother: I know that... But...
Mafuyu's Mother: Is that really your only reason...?
Mafuyu: What...?
Mafuyu's Father: What do you mean...?
Mafuyu's Mother: Hehe. Just asking.
Mafuyu's Mother: I understand why you feel anxious since everybody is working hard to get accepted, Mafuyu... However, I've also been told that a person's brain digests new information as they sleep.
Mafuyu's Mother: So, there wouldn't be much point in studying if you can't actually learn or memorize anything.
Mafuyu's Mother: Therefore, I believe you should study only when it's light out and sleep when you can.
Mafuyu's Father: Ah, I see. I agree with your mother. Especially since staying up late is bad for your health.
Mafuyu: But I...
Mafuyu's Mother: Oh? Is there more you'd like to say...?
Mafuyu: Um...
Mafuyu: (It didn't work...)
Mafuyu: (But I said that I didn't want to...)
Mafuyu: (If she gets her way and I'm not allowed to do anything with N25...)
Mafuyu: I...
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: (This place always helps calm my nerves...)
Mafuyu: (There's nothing... And it's so quiet...)
Mafuyu: (I don't have to think about anything...)
Mafuyu: Is this it...?
Mafuyu: Is there nothing else I can do...?
???: Looks like they were right...
KAITO: You're really okay with all this...?
